The paper proposes an end-to-end framework for visual tracking using convolutional neural networks (CNN), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The framework involves joint training of feature extraction and tracking process, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach also handles scale changes efficiently, which is a common problem in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
